name: Bra038899
subject: AT3G51430.1
At_description: Although this enzyme is predicted to encode a strictosidine synthase (SS), it lacks a conserved catalytic glutamate residue found in active SS enzymes and it is not expected to have SS activity.

name: Bra012899
subject: AT3G50440.1
At_description: Encodes a protein shown to have methyl jasmonate esterase activity in vitro. This protein does not act on methyl IAA, MeSA, MeGA4, or MEGA9 in vitro.

name: Bra011761
subject: AT4G37430.1
At_description: Encodes a member of the CYP81F cytochrome P450 monooxygenase subfamily.

name: Bra036465
subject: AT2G20340.1
At_description: Encodes an aromatic aldehyde synthase (AtAAS), which catalyzes the in vitro conversion of phenylalanine and 3,4-dihydroxy-L-phenylalanine to phenylacetaldehyde and dopaldehyde, respectively.

name: Bra008637
subject: AT5G66450.1
At_description: Encodes a phosphatidic acid phosphatase that can be detected in chloroplast membrane fractions. This gene (LPPepsilon2) and LPPepsilon1, appear to be less important for diacylglycerol formation in the plastids than LPPgamma.

name: Bra008840
subject: AT5G13280.1
At_description: Asp kinase inhibited by Lys and S-adenosylmethionine. Contains regulatory domains that belong to the ACT domain family, which allow binding to a extreme variety  of ligands. Can function as a monomer or as a dimer with acetohydroxyacid synthase (HSDH).

name: Bra025497
subject: AT5G41410.1
At_description: Homeodomain protein required for ovule identity.Loss of function mutations show homeotic conversion of integuments to carpels.Forms heterodimers with STM and KNAT1. Interacts with AG-SEP heterodimers is thought to restrict WUS expression. BEL interacts with MADS box dimers composed of SEP1(or SEP3) and AG, SHP1, SHP2 and STK. The interaction of BEL1 with AG-SEP3 is required for proper integument development and specification of integument identity.

name: Bra005332
subject: AT5G66450.1
At_description: Encodes a phosphatidic acid phosphatase that can be detected in chloroplast membrane fractions. This gene (LPPepsilon2) and LPPepsilon1, appear to be less important for diacylglycerol formation in the plastids than LPPgamma.

name: Bra037847
subject: AT5G67420.1
At_description: Encodes a LOB-domain protein involved in nitrogen metabolism and affecting leaf morphogenesis

name: Bra008684
subject: AT5G15630.1
At_description: Encodes a member of the COBRA family, similar to phytochelatin synthetase. Involved in secondary cell wall biosynthesis. Mutants make smaller plants with reduced levels of cellulose and cell wall sugars.

name: Bra022535
subject: AT3G45140.1
At_description: Chloroplast lipoxygenase required for wound-induced jasmonic acid accumulation in Arabidopsis.Mutants are resistant to Staphylococcus aureus and accumulate salicylic acid upon infection.

name: Bra023056
subject: AT2G36230.1
At_description: Encodes a BBMII isomerase involved in histidine  biosynthesis.

name: Bra026068
subject: AT1G16300.1
At_description: Encodes one of the chloroplast/plastid localized GAPDH isoforms (GAPCp1/At1g79530 and GAPCp2/At1g16300). gapcp double mutants display a drastic phenotype of arrested root development, dwarfism and sterility. GAPCps are important for the synthesis of serine in roots.

name: Bra024437
subject: AT5G67590.1
At_description: Mutant leaves have a reduced capacity for cold acclimation, appear water-soaked, leak electrolytes, and accumulate reactive oxygen species constitutively. Encode a protein with high similarity to the 18-kD Fe-S subunit of complex I (NADH dehydrogenase, EC 1.6.5.3) in the mitochondrial electron transfer chain.

name: Bra002619
subject: AT5G58770.1
At_description: AtCPT7 synthesizes medium-chain polyprenols of approximately 55 carbons in length. The enzyme utlizes geranylgeranyl pyrophosphate (GGPP) and isopentenyl pyrophosphate (IPP) as substrates. The enzymatic product accumulates into plastdial membranes

name: Bra002255
subject: AT5G19690.1
At_description: encodes an oligosaccharyl transferase involved response to high salt. Mutants are hypersensitive to high salt conditions

name: Bra008711
subject: AT5G15250.1
At_description: Encodes an FtsH protease that is localized to the chloroplast. AtFtsH6 is involved in the degradation of both Lhcb3 and Lhcb1 during senescence and high-light acclimation.

name: Bra008797
subject: AT5G13850.1
At_description: nascent polypeptide-associated complex subunit alpha-like protein 3
